      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-002",
      "start": 6.12,
      "end": 11.18,
      "text": "For more information, or to volunteer, please visit LibraVox.org.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-003",
      "start": 11.84,
      "end": 15.8,
      "text": "Recorded by Christine Doer, the known as Assa, Florida.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-004",
      "start": 18.56,
      "end": 21.8,
      "text": "Asop's Fables, the Dog, and the Cook.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-005",
      "start": 23.06,
      "end": 27.42,
      "text": "A rich man once invited a number of his friends and acquaintances to a banquet.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-006",
      "start": 27.42,
      "end": 33.34,
      "text": "His dog thought it would be a good opportunity to invite another dog, a friend of his.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-007",
      "start": 34.02,
      "end": 37.72,
      "text": "So he went to him and said, my master is giving a feast.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-008",
      "start": 38.58,
      "end": 41.5,
      "text": "There'll be a fine spread, so come and dine with me tonight.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-009",
      "start": 42.48,
      "end": 47.98,
      "text": "The dog thus invited came, and when he saw the preparations being made in the kitchen,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-010",
      "start": 48.48,
      "end": 51.66,
      "text": "he said to himself, my word, I'm in luck.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-011",
      "start": 52.34,
      "end": 56.28,
      "text": "I'll take care to eat enough tonight to last me two or three days.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-012",
      "start": 56.28,
      "end": 63.78,
      "text": "At the same time, he wagged his tail briskly by way of showing his friend how delighted he was to have been asked.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-013",
      "start": 64.94,
      "end": 70.76,
      "text": "But just then the Cook caught sight of him, and in his annoyance at seeing a strange dog in the kitchen,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-014",
      "start": 71.52,
      "end": 74.7,
      "text": "caught him up by the hind legs and threw him out of the window.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-015",
      "start": 75.66,
      "end": 80.84,
      "text": "He had a nasty fall and limped away as quickly as he could, howling dismally.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-016",
      "start": 81.72,
      "end": 87.06,
      "text": "Presently some other dogs met him and said, well, what sort of dinner did you get?",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-017",
      "start": 87.8,
      "end": 93.94,
      "text": "To which he replied, I had a splendid time, the wine was so good, and I drank so much of it,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-018",
      "start": 94.5,
      "end": 96.8,
      "text": "that I really don't remember how I got out of the house.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-019",
      "start": 98.04,
      "end": 101.6,
      "text": "Be shy of favors bestowed at the expense of others.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-020",
      "start": 102.84,
      "end": 104.9,
      "text": "End of the dog and the cook.",
      "note": ""
    }
  ],
